   1:Src/icm20948.c **** /**
   2:Src/icm20948.c ****  * icm20948.c — ICM-20948 + AK09916 driver (I2C1, 400 kHz)
   3:Src/icm20948.c ****  *
   4:Src/icm20948.c ****  * Pins:
   5:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   PB6  I2C1_SCL  AF4  →  ICM-20948 SCL  +  AK09916 ACL  (shared bus)
   6:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   PB7  I2C1_SDA  AF4  →  ICM-20948 SDA  +  AK09916 ADA  (shared bus)
   7:Src/icm20948.c ****  *
   8:Src/icm20948.c ****  * The Teyleten Robot breakout board has a solder bridge that disconnects
   9:Src/icm20948.c ****  * the AK09916 from the ICM-20948's internal I2C master and routes it to
  10:Src/icm20948.c ****  * the external ADA/ACL header pins.  Both devices therefore live on the
  11:Src/icm20948.c ****  * same I2C1 bus at separate 7-bit addresses (0x68 and 0x0C); they are
  12:Src/icm20948.c ****  * accessed with independent I2C transactions — no ICM-20948 Bank 3 or
  13:Src/icm20948.c ****  * I2C master configuration is required or used.
  14:Src/icm20948.c ****  *
  15:Src/icm20948.c ****  * I2C timing at PCLK1 = 80 MHz — TIMINGR = 0x10422F33:
  16:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   PRESC  = 1  → t_tick = 25 ns
  17:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   SCLDEL = 4  → t_SCLDEL = 125 ns  (spec ≥ 100 ns)
  18:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   SDADEL = 2  → t_SDADEL =  50 ns  (spec ≥   0 ns)
  19:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   SCLH   = 47 → t_SCLH  = 1200 ns  (spec ≥ 600 ns)
  20:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   SCLL   = 51 → t_SCLL  = 1300 ns  (spec ≥ 1300 ns)
  21:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   f_SCL  = 1 / ((48 + 52) × 25 ns) = 400 kHz
  22:Src/icm20948.c ****  *
  23:Src/icm20948.c ****  * Transfer model (polling, no DMA/IRQ):
  24:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   Write: START → addr+W → reg → data → STOP         (AUTOEND=1)
  25:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   Read:  START → addr+W → reg → TC
  26:Src/icm20948.c ****  *          → repeated START → addr+R → data[n] → STOP (AUTOEND=1)
  27:Src/icm20948.c ****  *
  28:Src/icm20948.c ****  * ICM-20948 register bank model:
  29:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   REG_BANK_SEL (0x7F) is present at the same address in all four banks.
  30:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   USER_BANK[5:4] selects the visible bank.  Output registers are in
  31:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   Bank 0; accel/gyro config registers are in Bank 2.  Bank 0 is always
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Taylor\AppData\Local\Temp\ccvpZWbF.s 			page 2


  32:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   restored on exit from any function that switches banks.
  33:Src/icm20948.c ****  *
  34:Src/icm20948.c ****  * AK09916 register model:
  35:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   The AK09916 is accessed directly at 0x0C; its registers are flat
  36:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   (no bank switching).  A single 9-byte burst starting at ST1 (0x10)
  37:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   covers ST1, HXL, HXH, HYL, HYH, HZL, HZH, TMPS, ST2.  Reading
  38:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   ST2 is mandatory — it releases the AK09916's internal data register
  39:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   latch so the next measurement can begin.
  40:Src/icm20948.c ****  *
  41:Src/icm20948.c ****  * Initialization sequence:
  42:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   1.  Configure GPIO (PB6/PB7) and I2C1
  43:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   2.  ICM-20948: select Bank 0, verify WHO_AM_I
  44:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   3.  ICM-20948: DEVICE_RESET, wake, CLKSEL=auto-PLL
  45:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   4.  ICM-20948: enable all axes (PWR_MGMT_2 = 0x00)
  46:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   5.  ICM-20948: Bank 2 — GYRO_CONFIG_1, ACCEL_CONFIG; restore Bank 0
  47:Src/icm20948.c ****  *   6.  AK09916: soft reset, wait, continuous mode 2 (20 Hz)
  48:Src/icm20948.c ****  */
  49:Src/icm20948.c **** 
